<span id="kadence-conversion-end-of-content"></span></main><link data-optimized="1" rel='stylesheet' id='kadence-footer-css' href='https://championsreviews.com/wp-content/litespeed/css/e0a28489fd994a1eb65337e5e0c9066a.css?ver=9066a' media='all' /><footer id="colophon" class="site-footer" role="contentinfo"><div class="site-footer-wrap"><div class="site-middle-footer-wrap site-footer-row-container site-footer-focus-item site-footer-row-layout-standard site-footer-row-tablet-layout-default site-footer-row-mobile-layout-default" data-section="kadence_customizer_footer_middle"><div class="site-footer-row-container-inner"><div class="site-container"><div class="site-middle-footer-inner-wrap site-footer-row site-footer-row-columns-2 site-footer-row-column-layout-right-golden site-footer-row-tablet-column-layout-default site-footer-row-mobile-column-layout-row ft-ro-dir-row ft-ro-collapse-normal ft-ro-t-dir-default ft-ro-m-dir-default ft-ro-lstyle-plain"><div class="site-footer-middle-section-1 site-footer-section footer-section-inner-items-1"><div class="footer-widget-area widget-area site-footer-focus-item footer-widget1 content-align-left content-tablet-align-center content-mobile-align-default content-valign-middle content-tablet-valign-default content-mobile-valign-default" data-section="sidebar-widgets-footer1"><div class="footer-widget-area-inner site-info-inner"><section id="block-12" class="widget widget_block widget_media_image"><figure class="wp-block-image size-full is-resized"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="1024" src="https://championsreviews.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/07/Background-Removed-ChampionsReviews.Com-Image-Logo-V5.5.png" alt="" class="wp-image-4410" style="width:110px;height:auto" srcset="https://championsreviews.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/07/Background-Removed-ChampionsReviews.Com-Image-Logo-V5.5.png 1024w, https://championsreviews.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/07/Background-Removed-ChampionsReviews.Com-Image-Logo-V5.5-300x300.png 300w, https://championsreviews.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/07/Background-Removed-ChampionsReviews.Com-Image-Logo-V5.5-150x150.png 150w, https://championsreviews.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/07/Background-Removed-ChampionsReviews.Com-Image-Logo-V5.5-768x768.png 768w, https://championsreviews.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/07/Background-Removed-ChampionsReviews.Com-Image-Logo-V5.5-600x600.png 600w, https://championsreviews.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/07/Background-Removed-ChampionsReviews.Com-Image-Logo-V5.5-200x200.png 200w, https://championsreviews.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/07/Background-Removed-ChampionsReviews.Com-Image-Logo-V5.5-100x100.png 100w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /></figure></section><section id="custom_html-3" class="widget_text widget widget_custom_html"><div class="textwidget custom-html-widget"><style>/* ===== Sitewide responsive fixes — mobile/tablet only unless noted, desktop untouched ===== */

/* 1. Floating social-share bar: applies at ALL sizes now (desktop included) -
   a leftover per-page "Custom CSS" hack on 9 pages was forcing
   position:fixed;top:850px;left:0 with no responsive scoping at all, fighting
   this rule on mobile/tablet and leaving desktop permanently pinned at an
   arbitrary pixel offset regardless of page length. That hack has been
   removed from each page's Custom CSS; this is now the single source of
   truth for the bar's layout on every device. */
.cb-social-sharing.floating {
  position: static !important;
  display: block !important;
  margin: 20px auto !important;
  width: 100% !important;
  max-width: 100% !important;
  left: auto !important;
  top: auto !important;
}
/* Real markup is <div class="cb-social-sharing floating"><ul class="cb-social-icons">
   <li><a>...</a></li>...</ul></div> - a list, not bare <a> tags. Reset the list's
   own default vertical block-stacking (list-style/margin/padding) and force a
   horizontal, wrapping, evenly-spaced, width-responsive row explicitly, since a
   flex container's default row direction can still lose to a more specific
   plugin/browser default without stating it outright. */
.cb-social-sharing.floating ul.cb-social-icons {
  display: flex !important;
  flex-direction: row !important;
  flex-wrap: wrap !important;
  justify-content: center !important;
  align-items: center !important;
  list-style: none !important;
  margin: 0 auto !important;
  padding: 0 !important;
  width: 100% !important;
  max-width: 420px !important;
  gap: 8px !important;
}
.cb-social-sharing.floating ul.cb-social-icons li {
  list-style: none !important;
  margin: 0 !important;
  padding: 0 !important;
  flex: 0 1 60px !important;
}
.cb-social-sharing.floating ul.cb-social-icons li a {
  display: flex !important;
  align-items: center !important;
  justify-content: center !important;
  width: 100% !important;
  max-width: 60px !important;
  height: 50px !important;
  margin: 0 auto !important;
}

/* 2. Subscribe form (WPForms #988 - used sitewide): email field always full
   width of its container; submit button full width on mobile/tablet only;
   consistent brand background color on all devices. Set directly (not just
   via the CSS custom properties) since the theme's own rule doesn't
   reference the variable for background-color. */
#wpforms-988 {
  --wpforms-background-color: #1F51FF !important;
  --wpforms-container-background-color: #1F51FF !important;
  --wpforms-button-background-color: #1F51FF !important;
  --wpforms-button-border-color: #1F51FF !important;
  background-color: #1F51FF !important;
}
#wpforms-988 .wpforms-container {
  background-color: #1F51FF !important;
}
#wpforms-988 .wpforms-submit {
  background-color: #1F51FF !important;
  border-color: #1F51FF !important;
}
#wpforms-988 input[type="email"] {
  width: 100% !important;
  max-width: 100% !important;
  box-sizing: border-box !important;
}
/* WPForms' own "Medium" field-size class caps input width on its own
   (independent of the type=email selector above) - override it directly so
   nothing about the field's built-in size setting can re-narrow it. */
#wpforms-988 .wpforms-field-medium {
  width: 100% !important;
  max-width: 100% !important;
  box-sizing: border-box !important;
}
#wpforms-988 .wpforms-field {
  width: 100% !important;
  box-sizing: border-box !important;
}
/* Labels sit directly on the new blue background - make them white so
   they're actually readable (was dark purple/near-invisible). */
#wpforms-988 .wpforms-field-label,
#wpforms-988 .wpforms-field-label-inline,
#wpforms-988 legend.wpforms-field-label,
#wpforms-988 .wpforms-required-label {
  color: #ffffff !important;
}
@media (max-width: 1024px) {
  #wpforms-988 .wpforms-submit {
    width: 100% !important;
    max-width: 100% !important;
    box-sizing: border-box !important;
  }
  .elementor-column.elementor-column:has(.elementor-widget-wpforms) {
    width: 100% !important;
    flex-basis: 100% !important;
    max-width: 100% !important;
  }
}

/* 3. Product comparison post gallery grid: use available width better on
   mobile/tablet instead of small ~150px thumbnails with wasted whitespace. */
@media (max-width: 600px) {
  div[style*="minmax(110px"] {
    grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr) !important;
    gap: 12px !important;
  }
}
@media (min-width: 601px) and (max-width: 1024px) {
  div[style*="minmax(110px"] {
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr) !important;
    gap: 14px !important;
  }
}

/* 4. Mobile/tablet header search bar: only show on the Home page, hidden on
   every other page/post. WordPress adds a "home" class to <body> only on
   the front page, so this targets everywhere else. */
@media (max-width: 1024px) {
  body:not(.home) .header-mobile-search-bar {
    display: none !important;
  }
}</style></div></section></div></div></div><div class="site-footer-middle-section-2 site-footer-section footer-section-inner-items-1"><div class="footer-widget-area widget-area site-footer-focus-item footer-navigation-wrap content-align-right content-tablet-align-center content-mobile-align-default content-valign-middle content-tablet-valign-default content-mobile-valign-middle footer-navigation-layout-stretch-false" data-section="kadence_customizer_footer_navigation"><div class="footer-widget-area-inner footer-navigation-inner"><nav id="footer-navigation" class="footer-navigation" role="navigation" aria-label="Footer"><div class="footer-menu-container"><ul id="footer-menu" class="menu"><li id="menu-item-2076" class="menu-item menu-item-type-post_type menu-item-object-page menu-item-2076"><a href="https://championsreviews.com/behavioral-policy/">⚙️Behavioral Policy</a></li><li id="menu-item-2720" class="menu-item menu-item-type-post_type menu-item-object-page menu-item-2720"><a href="https://championsreviews.com/about-us/">About Us</a></li><li id="menu-item-2074" class="menu-item menu-item-type-post_type menu-item-object-page menu-item-privacy-policy menu-item-2074"><a rel="privacy-policy" href="https://championsreviews.com/privacy-policy/">Privacy Policy</a></li><li id="menu-item-2075" class="menu-item menu-item-type-post_type menu-item-object-page menu-item-home current-menu-item page_item page-item-1425 current_page_item menu-item-2075"><a href="https://championsreviews.com/" aria-current="page">Homepage</a></li><li id="menu-item-2079" class="menu-item menu-item-type-post_type menu-item-object-page menu-item-2079"><a href="https://championsreviews.com/all-posts/">ChampionsReviews.com &#8211; All Post</a></li><li id="menu-item-2078" class="menu-item menu-item-type-post_type menu-item-object-page menu-item-2078"><a href="https://championsreviews.com/contacts/">Contacts</a></li><li id="menu-item-2080" class="menu-item menu-item-type-post_type menu-item-object-page m